.TP 2
.B
\fI{\&'Origin-State-Id\&', \fBUnsigned32()\fR\&}\fR\&:
Origin-State-Id is optional but, if configured, will be included in outgoing CER/CEA and DWR/DWA messages\&. Setting a value of \fI0\fR\& (zero) is equivalent to not setting a value, as documented in RFC 6733\&. The function \fBorigin_state_id/0\fR\& can be used as to retrieve a value that is computed when the diameter application is started\&.
